    <text id="B1141T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Cook enquires about the status of a woman's daughter who is in a hospital in
                    Richmond.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/>Office <abbr expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst Supt.</abbr>
                    Sub-<abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr> No. 10 7<hi rend="super">th</hi>
                    <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Department">Dept</abbr>, Potomac
                    <name type="recipient">Captain R. S. Lacey<lb/><abbr expan="Superintendent"
                        >Supt</abbr> 7<hi rend="super">th</hi>
                        <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr><lb/>Lynchburg <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-12-25"><abbr expan="December">Dec.</abbr> 25<hi
                                rend="super">th</hi> 1866</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Captain</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Esther Scott (<abbr expan="colored">cold</abbr>) has a daughter Susan Berry
                        (<abbr expan="colored">cold</abbr>) who is now in one of the General
                    Hospitals (W.S.) at Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>. The child has had
                    both limbs amputated and was taken from this place to Richmond in the early part
                    of January 1866.</p>

                <p>She wished to ascertain her address and also wishes to know if the girl will be
                    given her provided her present husband will go to Richmond for her.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obt.</abbr> Servant</salute>
                    <signed>Geo. T. Cook<lb/>1<hi rend="super">st</hi>
                        <abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lieut.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Veterans' Reserve Corps">V.R.C.</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst Supt.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
